description:
The Great Trains
Crown Publishers | 1973 | ISBN: 0517512084 | English | 268 pages | PDF | 52.7 MB

Trying to cover the history of passenger rail service and the most famous of passenger trains, worldwide, is a lofty ambition, and this book takes a decent stab at it. It's big - and covers a lot of ground. Each chapter has a different author, so you can get some specialized perspectives, rather than having one person try to handle everything. There are 340 illustrations, some in colour. If you are a true fan of passenger railroads, you should find this interesting
